channel.title: Kalteen - Rsps' at a whole new level
channel.description:
[center][IMG]http://i49.tinypic.com/21eahkp.gif[/img]
[size=12pt]All development progress will be logged on the website, which can be found [url=http://kalteen-rsps.com]here[/url]![/size]
[hr]
Hello Moparscape Members, I would like to introduce Kalteen because of its content its going to have a lot of features. I have lots of time but not only time money as well to spend on this project. This one of a kind server, is no ordinary server. It will have it's unique type off combat and it's most extraordinary economy system. The staff team for this server, will be chosen, by me and only me; the staff team will consist off the most professional people - they will be chosen when this is put out to the public.[/center]
[hr]
Updates:
[ul][li]New Donator Dungeon - in this dungeon it will consist off donator bosses, NPCs and such.[/li] [li]New Dialogue System.[/li] [li]Lots of mini content/dupes fixed.[/li][/ul]
[hr]
[i][b]Current Developers:[/b][/i]
[b]Leading Server/Client Developer:[/b] Jayden [b]Server/Client Developer:[/b] Arham 4 [b]Client Developer:[/b] [OPEN] [b]Website Developer:[/b] [OPEN]

item.dc:creator: @RevengePK RevengePK
item.description:
@RevengePK wrote:

[quote=“Arcik, post:188, topic:513019”][quote author=Hidendra]
4) New topics: You must post at least a few pictures of your Development. If you do not, we cannot believe you. You may substitute this with a video. Why pictures/video? So you have proof you did something. Also, topic titles must follow this.

  1. Projects: This is not the place to post minor projects, such as, changing spawn locations, adding a few commands then saying you will release. We want something more major than that, seeing as all you do to change spawn locations is change a number and you’re done. We don’t want to see that you can change a number, we want to see that you can create something that will change the server in such a way that it’ll make it funner and more enjoyable for the players, or that you can change the game code to make it more efficient at doing a certain task or to have more stability overall.
    [/quote]

I want to see some pics and information! Not a crappy blank webpage![/quote]

The webpage isn’t crappy! :’(

item.description:

[quote=“Tutorial, post:185, topic:513019”][quote author=Jayden. link=topic=631265.msg4287113#msg4287113 date=1366546139]
We’d like to release all of our updates in bulk. So you’ll hear from us in the next day or two!
[/quote]
That isn’t necessarily a good idea when you have a development thread. Stick to bulk update releases when you have the server released, so players have several things to get used to before the next bulk update.

Anyways, I’m sure you have the potential to go far with this project. I just wish I had more time and inspiration to work on my project.[/quote]

Thanks for this I have thought it over, and decided I will release every update we do.
